window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p>Originally published in 1895, Robert W. Chambers' <i>The King in Yellow</i> is a marvel of supernatural fiction that has influenced a number of writers in the genre, most notably H. P. Lovecraft. Its powerful combination of horror and lyrical prose has made it a classic, a masterpiece of weird fiction that endures to this day.</p> <p>There is a book that is shrouded in mystery. Some even say it's a myth. Within its pages is a play - one that brings madness and despair to all who read it. It is the play of the <i>King in Yellow,</i> and it will haunt you for the rest of your days.</p> <p><i>The King in Yellow </i>is a collection of stories interwoven loosely by the elements of the play, including the central figure himself.</p>"; 
